Sentencas: The performance of nickel-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported cell with CO-CO2 feed was evaluated.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: The aim of this work is to examine carbon formation on the Ni-SDC anode when feeding with CO under conditions when carbon deposition is thermodynamically favoured.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: Electrochemical tests were conducted at intermediate temperatures (550-700 degrees C) using 20 and 40% CO concentrations.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: Cell operating with 40% CO at 600-700 degrees C provided maximum power densities of 239-270 mW cm(-2), 1.5 times smaller than that achieved with humidified H-2.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: Much lower maximum power densities were attained with 20% CO (50-88 mW cm(-2)).
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: Some degradation was observed during the 6 h galvanostatic operation at 0.1 A cm(-2) with 40% CO fuel at 550 degrees C which is believed due to the accumulation of carbon at the anode.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: The degradation in cell potential occurred at a rate of 4.5 mV h(-2), but it did not lead to cell collapse.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: EDX mapping at the cross-section of the anode revealed that carbon formed in the Ni-SDC cell was primarily deposited in the anode section close to the fuel entry point.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO

Sentencas: Carbon was not detected at the electrolyte-anode interface and the middle of the anode, allowing the cell to continue operation with CO fuel without a catastrophic failure.
Titulo: Ni-samaria-doped ceria (Ni-SDC) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) operating with CO
